cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.AL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper investigates the performance of a heuristic when distributively implemented in a network. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper deals with a mobile agent visiting every node in a network. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the worst-case performance of the nearest neighbor heuristic. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the paper deals with network traversal. 
- cs.AL (Computational Geometry) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the distances between nodes in a network.
